PtolC Installation Guide
========================

Quick path (Ubuntu 22.04 / 24.04 / Mint 21+):

  sudo apt install build-essential libxml2-dev
  cd PtolC
  make
  make corpus          # download WordNet + build baseline checkpoint

The binary is ./ptolemy.  For system-wide install:

  sudo make install PREFIX=/usr/local

For user-local install:

  make install PREFIX=$HOME/.local

Then add ~/.local/bin to PATH if not already present:

  echo 'export PATH="$HOME/.local/bin:$PATH"' >> ~/.bashrc
  source ~/.bashrc


OPTIONAL DEPENDENCIES
---------------------

libxml2 (HTML/XML extraction):
  sudo apt install libxml2-dev
  Detected automatically by pkg-config at build time.
  Without it, .html/.htm/.xml/.svg files are ingested as plain text.

pdftotext (PDF extraction):
  sudo apt install poppler-utils
  Without it, .pdf files are skipped.

catdoc (.doc extraction):
  sudo apt install catdoc
  Without it, .doc files are skipped.

pandoc (.docx/.odt/.rtf extraction):
  sudo apt install pandoc
  Without it, .docx/.odt/.rtf files are skipped.


CMAKE BUILD
-----------

Requires cmake >= 3.16:

  sudo apt install cmake
  cmake -B build -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release
  cmake --build build
  sudo cmake --install build

Override install prefix:

  cmake -B build -DCMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX=$HOME/.local
  cmake --build build
  cmake --install build

CMake auto-detects libxml2 and reports its status at configure time.
The compile_commands.json for clangd is written to build/.


CORPUS (BASELINE CHECKPOINT)
-----------------------------

The corpus target downloads WordNet 3.1 via NLTK and ingests all
153,888 lemma definitions:

  make corpus

Requires Python 3 and pip:

  sudo apt install python3 python3-pip
  pip3 install --break-system-packages nltk

The resulting checkpoint is saved to ~/.ptolemy/monad_wordnet.bin (13 MB).
Run once.  The checkpoint persists across updates — only rebuild after
expanding N with checkpoint_expand.


SYSTEMD (OPTIONAL)
------------------

Install user-level socket and service units:

  make install-systemd

Enable the daemon:

  systemctl --user enable --now ptolemy.socket

The daemon auto-starts on demand when ptolemy -D is called.
Socket path: ~/.ptolemy/ptolemy.sock


ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES
---------------------

  PTOLEMY_HOME         Override ~/.ptolemy/ (home directory)
  PTOLEMY_CHECKPOINT   Override checkpoint path directly


UNINSTALL
---------

  sudo make install PREFIX=/usr/local   # find installed files
  sudo rm /usr/local/bin/ptolemy
  sudo rm /usr/local/share/man/man1/ptolemy.1.gz
  sudo rm /usr/local/share/man/man5/ptolemyignore.5.gz

Runtime data (checkpoint, logs) lives in ~/.ptolemy/ and is not touched
by any install or uninstall target.
